      • ActivityAction

        public ActivityAction(java.lang.String packageName,
              android.net.Uri uri)
        Constructs an ActivityAction given a package name and Uri. The Uri query parameters are parsed and added to the Intent as extras.

      • ActivityAction

        public ActivityAction(java.lang.String packageName,
              android.net.Uri uri,
              android.os.Bundle extras)
        Constructs an ActivityAction given a package name and Uri. The Uri query parameters are parsed and added to the Intent as extras. The bundle is used as the initial extras. For any collisions in the keys, the uri will take priority.

      • ActivityAction

        public ActivityAction(android.content.Intent intent)
        Constructs an ActivityAction given a fully initialized Intent. The intent will be passed as a parameter to the Context.startActivity(android.content.Intent) method.
